806
01:01:50,973 --> 01:01:52,224
Where, over there?

807
01:01:52,308 --> 01:01:53,142
Yes!

808
01:02:01,358 --> 01:02:03,444
Look, the Chain Bridge, Michael!

809
01:03:30,322 --> 01:03:31,490
What's it say?

810
01:03:31,573 --> 01:03:33,242
Just a minute, it's very long.

811
01:03:33,325 --> 01:03:35,786
Palmer indubitably imposter.

812
01:03:35,869 --> 01:03:37,579
Hurray!

813
01:03:37,663 --> 01:03:38,580
Let's go and tell Dad!

814
01:03:38,664 --> 01:03:39,707
Right!

815
01:03:39,790 --> 01:03:42,626
When this man,
Palmer, came to Italy,

816
01:03:42,710 --> 01:03:44,753
he called himself.

817
01:03:44,837 --> 01:03:48,841
We feared that some of our
priceless antique relics

818
01:03:48,924 --> 01:03:50,092
- would disappear.
- Yes?

819
01:03:51,385 --> 01:03:53,137
Oh, oh, they're here, are they?

820
01:03:53,220 --> 01:03:53,971
Well, tell 'em I'll be right out.

821
01:03:54,054 --> 01:03:55,681
An Etruscan tomb.

822
01:03:55,764 --> 01:03:57,182
The tomb was empty.

823
01:03:58,392 --> 01:04:02,187
And another thing, our fingerprint experts

824
01:04:02,271 --> 01:04:03,480
have reached the point,

825
01:04:04,356 --> 01:04:06,066
- frequently ascertain...
- Here he is.

826
01:04:06,150 --> 01:04:08,026
Dad, you know that
man we told you about?

827
01:04:08,110 --> 01:04:10,028
He really is a fraud.

828
01:04:10,112 --> 01:04:10,904
What man, darling?

829
01:04:10,988 --> 01:04:11,947
The man we phoned about.

830
01:04:12,030 --> 01:04:13,866
We think he stole the golden head.

831
01:04:15,284 --> 01:04:16,910
Well, surely you've heard about that, Dad.

832
01:04:16,994 --> 01:04:18,078
Of course I have, the Hungarian police

833
01:04:18,162 --> 01:04:19,329
are talking about nothing else.

834
01:04:19,413 --> 01:04:21,790
If you're so sure, why didn't
you get in touch with them?

835
01:04:21,874 --> 01:04:23,125
We tried like mad.

836
01:04:23,208 --> 01:04:24,251
They won't believe us.

837
01:04:24,334 --> 01:04:27,129
Milly tried to tell them about
them at Gyor and Esztergom,

838
01:04:27,212 --> 01:04:28,380
but they just won't believe us.

839
01:04:28,464 --> 01:04:30,382
So we sent a cable to London,

840
01:04:30,466 --> 01:04:32,092
and we found out there's no such man.

841
01:04:32,176 --> 01:04:33,594
I mean, no such address,

842
01:04:33,677 --> 01:04:35,804
and so we sent a photo from Visegrad.

843
01:04:35,888 --> 01:04:36,638
Who the devil to?

844
01:04:36,722 --> 01:04:38,223
A friend.

845
01:04:39,475 --> 01:04:40,809
What are you all talking about?

846
01:04:40,893 --> 01:04:43,896
It's true, he gave us a
false address in St. James's.

847
01:04:46,023 --> 01:04:47,232
You mean he's English?

848
01:04:48,692 --> 01:04:49,443
What are you trying to do,

849
01:04:49,526 --> 01:04:51,904
disgrace me with the
British delegation here?

850
01:04:53,363 --> 01:04:55,073
Anna, for heaven's sake,
get them out of here

851
01:04:55,157 --> 01:04:56,450
and show them Budapest, or something.

852
01:04:56,533 --> 01:04:58,702
And Milly, will you
please leave the police

853
01:04:58,786 --> 01:05:00,829
to do their own job?

854
01:05:00,913 --> 01:05:03,791
But I'm positive I
saw it in the caravan,

855
01:05:03,874 --> 01:05:05,709
and now they're following us.

856
01:05:05,793 --> 01:05:09,421
Milly, that room there
is full of police officials

857
01:05:09,505 --> 01:05:10,547
from all over the world.

858
01:05:10,631 --> 01:05:12,132
Are you trying to tell
me that you can do better

859
01:05:12,216 --> 01:05:14,051
than all of them put together?

860
01:05:14,134 --> 01:05:17,429
Dad, take this picture
just in case, huh?

861
01:05:17,513 --> 01:05:18,680
Oh, all right.

862
01:05:18,764 --> 01:05:20,599
Stevenson, be a good
fellow and come and show me

863
01:05:20,682 --> 01:05:22,142
where the notes are on the
forgery case, will you?

864
01:05:22,226 --> 01:05:23,519
We'll need them in a jiffy.

865
01:05:23,602 --> 01:05:25,103
- Hello, you lot.
- Good afternoon.

866
01:05:25,187 --> 01:05:26,355
- Come on, old man!
- Goodbye.

867
01:05:26,438 --> 01:05:27,272
Goodbye.

868
01:05:29,858 --> 01:05:32,945
Why is Dad so much more helpful
in print than in real life?

869
01:05:34,863 --> 01:05:37,032
There are plenty of things
to see on Saturday afternoon.

870
01:05:37,115 --> 01:05:38,492
Where would you like to go?

871
01:05:39,868 --> 01:05:41,245
The movies.

872
01:05:41,328 --> 01:05:42,412
Football.

873
01:05:42,496 --> 01:05:44,331
All right, football.

874
01:05:44,414 --> 01:05:46,708
Number seven bus will take
you right to the stadium

875
01:05:46,792 --> 01:05:49,294
and you can take a taxi back to the boat.

876
01:05:49,378 --> 01:05:51,046
What are we grown-ups gonna do?

877
01:05:52,506 --> 01:05:53,757
You will see.

878
01:05:55,133 --> 01:05:57,344
Good afternoon,
ladies and gentlemen.

879
01:05:57,427 --> 01:05:59,346
Welcome to the Turf Club.

880
01:05:59,429 --> 01:06:02,683
Well, Basil, how we
gonna bet without losing?

881
01:06:03,517 --> 01:06:05,602
Very simple, we won't use our money.

882
01:06:05,686 --> 01:06:06,895
Well, then whose?

883
01:06:08,021 --> 01:06:08,856
His.

884
01:06:10,858 --> 01:06:11,984
Go on, get it.

885
01:06:12,067 --> 01:06:13,443
Lesson number four.

886
01:06:30,752 --> 01:06:31,837
I didn't get it.

887
01:06:31,920 --> 01:06:33,171
I know.

888
01:06:33,255 --> 01:06:34,715
Now, Lionel, pay attention.

889
01:06:34,798 --> 01:06:37,759
This is absolutely the last
time I'm going to show you.

890
01:07:00,407 --> 01:07:01,742
See what I mean?

891
01:07:06,038 --> 01:07:06,955
Oh!

892
01:07:07,039 --> 01:07:08,290
Now, give it back.

893
01:07:08,373 --> 01:07:09,458
Back?

894
01:07:09,541 --> 01:07:11,919
Give it back and look sad.

895
01:07:12,002 --> 01:07:13,211
Don't worry, I will.

896
01:07:14,129 --> 01:07:15,047
You're kidding, huh?

897
01:07:15,130 --> 01:07:16,465
No, no, go on.

898
01:07:17,716 --> 01:07:18,508
But...

899
01:07:18,592 --> 01:07:20,677
And don't forget to look sad.

900
01:07:20,761 --> 01:07:22,387
Don't forget to...

901
01:08:09,059 --> 01:08:10,018
Okay.

902
01:08:10,102 --> 01:08:13,021
Now, look, the big payoff comes
if you can pick number one

903
01:08:13,105 --> 01:08:14,773
and number two.

904
01:08:14,856 --> 01:08:17,734
So we're gonna bet that
on number five and six.

905
01:08:17,818 --> 01:08:18,568
They're longshots.

906
01:08:18,652 --> 01:08:21,029
That' right, big risk, big money.

907
01:08:21,113 --> 01:08:24,199
Now, you take that and
we bet half on number six

908
01:08:24,282 --> 01:08:26,618
to come in first, and the
other half on number five

909
01:08:26,702 --> 01:08:28,662
to come in second, okay, got that?

910
01:08:28,745 --> 01:08:31,832
Yes, six to come in first
and five to come in second.

911
01:08:31,915 --> 01:08:32,666
Right.

912
01:08:32,749 --> 01:08:34,668
Six to come in first,
five to come in second.

913
01:08:34,751 --> 01:08:38,880
And six to come in first,
and five to come in second.

914
01:08:38,964 --> 01:08:42,092
And six to come in first,
and five to come in second.

915
01:08:42,175 --> 01:08:44,845
Six to come in first and
five to come in second.

916
01:08:44,928 --> 01:08:46,847
And six to come in, oh!

917
01:08:50,767 --> 01:08:55,522
Five to come in first and
six to come in second.

918
01:09:06,742 --> 01:09:08,702
The horses are
approaching the starting line.

919
01:10:39,751 --> 01:10:41,253
Can't win 'em all, you know?

920
01:10:41,336 --> 01:10:42,379
You were silly, Basil.

921
01:10:42,462 --> 01:10:45,549
You should have bet five
and six, not six and five.

922
01:10:45,632 --> 01:10:47,843
The results of the first race are

923
01:10:47,926 --> 01:10:49,594
number five wins.

924
01:10:49,678 --> 01:10:51,972
Lionel, you made a mistake!

925
01:10:52,055 --> 01:10:54,057
I'm sorry about that, Basil.

926
01:10:55,016 --> 01:10:56,726
Well, this time, I'll forgive you.

927
01:10:56,810 --> 01:10:58,436
Come on, let's collect our money.

928
01:11:02,649 --> 01:11:05,485
I'm sorry, I cannot
pay out on this ticket.

929
01:11:05,569 --> 01:11:06,778
It's a torn ticket.

930
01:11:06,862 --> 01:11:08,572
Oh, come now, I paid for it.

931
01:11:08,655 --> 01:11:09,948
Just a minute.

932
01:11:10,031 --> 01:11:10,949
Hey, what's he sayin'?

933
01:11:11,032 --> 01:11:12,742
He says he can't pay
out on a torn ticket.

934
01:11:12,826 --> 01:11:13,577
Oh!

935
01:11:13,660 --> 01:11:15,120
Would you mind letting us take a picture

936
01:11:15,203 --> 01:11:16,413
for The Evening Gazette?

937
01:11:16,496 --> 01:11:17,247
Sure.

938
01:11:17,330 --> 01:11:18,165
If it's not too much trouble.

939
01:11:18,248 --> 01:11:19,082
Okay.

940
01:11:20,125 --> 01:11:21,835
There you are.

941
01:11:21,918 --> 01:11:22,919
Very good!

942
01:11:25,589 --> 01:11:26,673
There it is.

943
01:11:26,756 --> 01:11:29,009
Can I have both your names
so I have a record of it

944
01:11:29,092 --> 01:11:29,926
in my files?

945
01:11:52,032 --> 01:11:53,700
Yes, what is it?

946
01:11:53,783 --> 01:11:58,121
The Honorable Augustus
Brookington-Smythe

947
01:11:58,205 --> 01:12:00,540
wishes to see you on
an urgent matter, sir.

948
01:12:00,624 --> 01:12:02,918
I don't know any Augustus Thingamabob.

949
01:12:04,336 --> 01:12:05,587
Oh.

950
01:12:05,670 --> 01:12:06,630
Now, wait a minute.

951
01:12:07,631 --> 01:12:09,549
Yes, of course, that'll be Diana's boy.

952
01:12:11,551 --> 01:12:13,011
All right, show him in.

953
01:12:13,094 --> 01:12:14,512
Very well, sir.

954
01:12:17,724 --> 01:12:18,975
Good afternoon, sir.

955
01:12:19,059 --> 01:12:21,561
My mother asked to be remembered to you.

956
01:12:21,645 --> 01:12:23,939
When I mentioned my
particular problem to her,

957
01:12:24,022 --> 01:12:25,941
she said you'd be sure to help

958
01:12:26,024 --> 01:12:27,609
if I reminded you of the evening

959
01:12:27,692 --> 01:12:30,320
of Queen Charlotte's Ball in 1951.

960
01:12:31,488 --> 01:12:36,076
Oh, that's the way it is, eh?

961
01:12:36,159 --> 01:12:39,579
Still, it was a rather wonderful evening.

962
01:12:42,123 --> 01:12:44,042
Right, now, what can I do for you?

963
01:12:46,795 --> 01:12:48,296
Could you tell me if these men

964
01:12:48,380 --> 01:12:50,423
are in your international rogues gallery?

965
01:12:52,050 --> 01:12:54,594
Oh, yes, I think we might manage that.

966
01:12:54,678 --> 01:12:55,887
Anything else?

967
01:12:55,971 --> 01:12:58,556
Well, sir, if the resultant information

968
01:12:58,640 --> 01:13:01,101
were to prove interesting,

969
01:13:01,184 --> 01:13:03,395
I assume you could get
a message to Budapest

970
01:13:03,478 --> 01:13:04,646
quicker than I could.

971
01:13:04,771 --> 01:13:08,650
Well, yes, of course, I
mean, did you say Budapest?

972
01:13:08,733 --> 01:13:10,360
Yes, I did, to the police there.

973
01:13:10,443 --> 01:13:14,489
Now, on second thought, for
the sake of national prestige,

974
01:13:14,572 --> 01:13:18,034
it might be preferable to
get it to old man Stevenson.

975
01:13:18,118 --> 01:13:18,868
Who?

976
01:13:18,952 --> 01:13:21,454
Stevenson, he's at the
International Conference

977
01:13:21,538 --> 01:13:22,664
on Criminal Law.

978
01:13:22,747 --> 01:13:24,040
You know him.

979
01:13:24,124 --> 01:13:25,542
Why, yes, of course.

980
01:13:26,418 --> 01:13:27,794
Now, look here, young man,

981
01:13:27,877 --> 01:13:30,088
there are quite a few
questions I'd like to ask you.

982
01:13:30,171 --> 01:13:32,841
What about the photograph first?

983
01:13:32,924 --> 01:13:34,259
What?

984
01:13:34,342 --> 01:13:36,011
Oh, photograph, yes.

985
01:14:11,796 --> 01:14:13,882
Well, it's still there.

986
01:14:41,034 --> 01:14:42,202
It's Palmer!

987
01:14:44,287 --> 01:14:45,872
It is Palmer.

988
01:14:45,955 --> 01:14:47,832
For once, you're not seeing things.

989
01:14:47,916 --> 01:14:49,250
I wonder what it says.

990
01:14:51,544 --> 01:14:54,381
Gellert Hotel, we can understand that.

991
01:14:54,464 --> 01:14:56,132
Gellert Hotel, that's near us!

992
01:15:08,019 --> 01:15:09,604
There's somebody on our boat!

993
01:15:09,687 --> 01:15:10,897
Hey, what are you doing?

994
01:15:23,618 --> 01:15:27,288
You dirty rotten,
stay away from our boat!

995
01:15:28,832 --> 01:15:30,458
I wonder what they were doing.

996
01:15:32,043 --> 01:15:33,044
Let's take a look.

997
01:15:40,468 --> 01:15:41,428
I wonder what it is.

998
01:15:41,511 --> 01:15:42,387
I don't know.

999
01:15:47,392 --> 01:15:48,810
The golden head!

1000
01:16:08,371 --> 01:16:11,291
Those men must have been
in Palmer's gang, but why?

1001
01:16:11,374 --> 01:16:14,169
Don't you see, things
got too hot for them,

1002
01:16:14,252 --> 01:16:16,004
so they planted it on us.

1003
01:16:16,087 --> 01:16:17,672
Police would never fall for that.

1004
01:16:17,755 --> 01:16:18,506
Why not?

1005
01:16:18,590 --> 01:16:20,175
They didn't believe us before.

1006
01:16:20,258 --> 01:16:21,593
Wait till Michael and Anna see this.

1007
01:16:21,676 --> 01:16:24,179
You can't show it to Michael and Anna!

1008
01:16:24,262 --> 01:16:25,221
What's the matter with you?

1009
01:16:25,305 --> 01:16:26,556
Of course we can.

1010
01:16:26,639 --> 01:16:27,557
Don't you see?

1011
01:16:27,640 --> 01:16:29,559
Anna's Hungarian, and she'd
have to tell the police,

1012
01:16:29,642 --> 01:16:32,020
and Daddy told us to lay off Palmer.

1013
01:16:32,103 --> 01:16:34,022
Hmm, what can we do then?

1014
01:16:35,231 --> 01:16:37,984
Palmer and his gang planted it on us,

1015
01:16:38,067 --> 01:16:39,694
so we must go to the Gellert Hotel

1016
01:16:39,777 --> 01:16:43,323
and plant it on Palmer
instead, then go to the police.

1017
01:16:43,406 --> 01:16:45,742
We better leave a note
for Michael and Anna.

1018
01:16:45,825 --> 01:16:48,036
They'll be in a fit
wondering where we've been.

1019
01:16:59,797 --> 01:17:01,299
Is this more like it, Michael?

1020
01:17:01,382 --> 01:17:02,217
Yes, it is.

1021
01:17:03,593 --> 01:17:06,387
I'm sorry your friend
wasn't able to come with us.

1022
01:17:06,471 --> 01:17:08,848
Oh, Michael, you're not a good liar.

1023
01:17:08,932 --> 01:17:09,766
No, I'm not.

1024
01:17:12,018 --> 01:17:15,188
The truth is, I wanted
to be alone with you.

1025
01:17:36,376 --> 01:17:38,628
Let's get outta here.

1026
01:17:38,711 --> 01:17:39,754
Come on.

1027
01:17:58,356 --> 01:18:00,650
Put that note where
they'll be sure to see it.

1028
01:18:08,199 --> 01:18:09,117
Right, ready?

1029
01:18:20,461 --> 01:18:22,297
There's Dad, what are we gonna do?

1030
01:18:22,380 --> 01:18:23,214
Hide it!

1031
01:18:28,344 --> 01:18:29,971
- Hello, Dad.
- Where are Michael and Anna?

1032
01:18:30,054 --> 01:18:33,224
Oh, they had something special
to see, some kinda museum.

1033
01:18:33,308 --> 01:18:34,892
They shouldn't be too long.

1034
01:18:34,976 --> 01:18:36,394
Are you up to something?

1035
01:18:36,477 --> 01:18:37,979
No, Daddy.

1036
01:18:38,062 --> 01:18:38,938
You've stopped all this cops

1037
01:18:39,022 --> 01:18:40,148
and robbers nonsense, have you?

1038
01:18:40,273 --> 01:18:41,899
Yes, Daddy.

1039
01:18:41,983 --> 01:18:42,984
Thank goodness for that.

1040
01:18:43,109 --> 01:18:45,236
I say, old man, you are
watching the time, aren't you?

1041
01:18:45,320 --> 01:18:47,196
Oh, yes, now, we're
off for a special showing

1042
01:18:47,280 --> 01:18:48,740
of the ballet with the other delegates.

1043
01:18:48,823 --> 01:18:52,410
Now, we'll take you next
time if you're good, right?

1044
01:18:52,493 --> 01:18:53,620
Yes, Daddy.

1045
01:18:53,745 --> 01:18:54,662
Right.

1046
01:18:54,746 --> 01:18:55,580
Cheerio.

1047
01:19:03,379 --> 01:19:05,923
Oh, dear.

1048
01:19:21,356 --> 01:19:22,398
Hey, what's this?

1049
01:19:24,734 --> 01:19:26,819
Got the golden head.

1050
01:19:26,903 --> 01:19:29,739
Planting it on Palmer,
then telling police.

1051
01:19:29,822 --> 01:19:31,949
Don't contact police till we're ready.

1052
01:19:32,033 --> 01:19:34,369
If you do, it will spoil everything.

1053
01:19:34,452 --> 01:19:36,162
Do you really think they have the head?

1054
01:19:36,245 --> 01:19:37,455
I don't know.

1055
01:19:37,538 --> 01:19:41,376
Crazy kids, they imagine
anything, specially Milly.

1056
01:19:43,336 --> 01:19:45,254
Well, we'll just have to wait.

1057
01:20:06,401 --> 01:20:07,610
Excuse me, please.

1058
01:20:08,444 --> 01:20:09,404
What do you want?

1059
01:20:09,487 --> 01:20:11,155
We have something to
leave for Mr. Palmer.

1060
01:20:11,239 --> 01:20:12,740
He's a friend of my father's.

1061
01:20:12,824 --> 01:20:13,866
Palmer?

1062
01:20:13,950 --> 01:20:15,993
Oh, yes, he's in room 244.

1063
01:20:16,077 --> 01:20:17,412
He's at dinner now.

1064
01:20:18,371 --> 01:20:20,915
If you want to see him,
you'll have to wait a while.

1065
01:20:20,998 --> 01:20:21,833
Just a minute.

1066
01:20:47,066 --> 01:20:49,152
It's locked, what can we do?

1067
01:20:53,281 --> 01:20:54,949
Do you speak English?

1068
01:20:55,032 --> 01:20:56,200
A little.

1069
01:20:56,284 --> 01:20:57,744
We have a present for Mr. Palmer.

1070
01:20:57,827 --> 01:20:59,662
Do you think we could leave it?

1071
01:21:01,706 --> 01:21:02,540
Yes.

1072
01:21:15,094 --> 01:21:15,970
Thank you.

1073
01:21:18,139 --> 01:21:19,182
Keep watch on the door while I try

1074
01:21:19,265 --> 01:21:20,725
and find a good hiding place.

1075
01:21:33,070 --> 01:21:34,113
Someone's coming!

1076
01:21:34,197 --> 01:21:35,156
It's those other two!

1077
01:21:35,239 --> 01:21:37,283
But I haven't hidden the head yet!

1078
01:21:37,366 --> 01:21:38,701
Under the bed!

1079
01:22:47,228 --> 01:22:49,689
Good work, Milly, but Palmer
will only let them out again.

1080
01:22:49,814 --> 01:22:52,275
Well, I had to do something.

1081
01:22:57,613 --> 01:23:00,491
Either making these key holes
lower or I'm gettin' taller.

1082
01:24:03,804 --> 01:24:04,639
Hey!

1083
01:24:05,681 --> 01:24:07,308
There's a picture of Palmer here.

1084
01:24:09,101 --> 01:24:10,895
Anna, what does this say?

1085
01:24:15,149 --> 01:24:17,401
They won a lot of
money at the racetrack.

1086
01:24:18,653 --> 01:24:21,739
He's staying at the Gellert Hotel.

1087
01:24:21,822 --> 01:24:23,199
Anna, did you buy that paper?

1088
01:24:23,282 --> 01:24:24,241
No.

1089
01:24:24,325 --> 01:24:26,035
Well, then the kids must have done it,

1090
01:24:26,118 --> 01:24:28,329
and they know Palmer's
at the Gellert Hotel.

1091
01:24:29,372 --> 01:24:30,206
Come on.

1092
01:24:37,505 --> 01:24:39,090
What time should I set it for?

1093
01:24:39,173 --> 01:24:40,925
Oh, about 3:30.

1094
01:24:42,009 --> 01:24:43,386
AM or PM?

1095
01:24:43,469 --> 01:24:44,303
Either one.

1096
01:24:48,307 --> 01:24:51,602
Why can't we sleep with our clothes off?

1097
01:24:51,686 --> 01:24:54,438
He travels fastest who travels dressed.

1098
01:24:55,856 --> 01:24:56,774
That's beautiful.

1099
01:24:57,733 --> 01:24:59,318
Did a great man say that?

1100
01:24:59,402 --> 01:25:00,528
Yes, I did.

1101
01:25:02,071 --> 01:25:03,864
Basil, don't think that I'm not grateful

1102
01:25:03,948 --> 01:25:06,450
to learn these beautiful
things and to learn a trade,

1103
01:25:06,534 --> 01:25:09,453
but when we come to a
very nice hotel like this,

1104
01:25:09,537 --> 01:25:10,705
I don't like to sneak in.

1105
01:25:10,788 --> 01:25:12,623
Why can't I be registered?

1106
01:25:12,707 --> 01:25:15,543
It's just a simple matter of economics.

1107
01:25:15,626 --> 01:25:19,380
Other men my age have
wives and children, a home.

1108
01:25:19,505 --> 01:25:21,215
It isn't as though
you're not living anywhere.

1109
01:25:21,298 --> 01:25:22,800
You're living with me.

1110
01:25:22,883 --> 01:25:24,802
Then why can't I be registered?

1111
01:25:25,970 --> 01:25:27,388
It's too expensive.

1112
01:25:28,973 --> 01:25:30,766
You always charge me.

1113
01:25:31,934 --> 01:25:33,728
I never charge you the full rate.

1114
01:25:35,312 --> 01:25:36,939
That's right, you don't ever.

1115
01:25:38,733 --> 01:25:40,151
I'm sorry I mentioned it.

1116
01:25:41,360 --> 01:25:42,862
Goodnight, Basil.

1117
01:25:42,945 --> 01:25:44,613
Goodnight, Lionel.

1118
01:27:07,863 --> 01:27:09,198
Hey, hey, hey!

1119
01:27:12,743 --> 01:27:14,370
I beg your pardon.

1120
01:27:14,453 --> 01:27:15,538
I'm so sorry.

1121
01:27:16,622 --> 01:27:17,373
Excuse me.

1122
01:27:21,085 --> 01:27:22,378
I beg your pardon.

1123
01:27:23,838 --> 01:27:24,922
I'm so sorry.

1124
01:27:25,798 --> 01:27:27,049
I beg your pardon.

1125
01:27:49,655 --> 01:27:51,991
It's the continental exchange, old man.

1126
01:27:52,074 --> 01:27:54,952
They want to know if you'll
accept a call at midnight.

1127
01:27:55,035 --> 01:27:55,786
Who from, the Yard?

1128
01:27:55,870 --> 01:27:57,454
Yes, old man.

1129
01:27:57,538 --> 01:27:58,289
Wonder what it's about.

1130
01:27:58,372 --> 01:28:00,332
Something about a photograph
of an Englishman here.

1131
01:28:00,416 --> 01:28:01,500
Oh, no!

1132
01:28:01,584 --> 01:28:02,418
Why, did we send it?

1133
01:28:02,501 --> 01:28:04,712
No, but I have a
pretty good idea who did.

1134
01:28:04,795 --> 01:28:06,130
I'll take the call from my hotel.

1135
01:28:06,213 --> 01:28:07,882
Are you joking, at midnight?

1136
01:28:07,965 --> 01:28:09,884
But I'm taking you out to
the Budapest Bar after this!

1137
01:28:09,967 --> 01:28:11,135
- Oh, no, no.
- My dear fellow,

1138
01:28:11,218 --> 01:28:12,136
it's the hottest place in town!

1139
01:28:12,219 --> 01:28:13,679
- I really can't.
- Of course you can.

1140
01:28:13,762 --> 01:28:15,222
It's absolutely jumping!

1141
01:28:16,473 --> 01:28:17,766
- Is it?
- Mm-hmm.

1142
01:28:17,850 --> 01:28:19,560
Oh.

1143
01:28:19,643 --> 01:28:20,895
All right, I'll take the call from there.

1144
01:28:20,978 --> 01:28:24,148
Oh, yes, of course, yes, yes.

1145
01:28:24,231 --> 01:28:27,193
Hello?

1146
01:29:15,115 --> 01:29:17,952
Excuse me, do you have
a Mr. Palmer staying here?

1147
01:29:18,953 --> 01:29:22,581
Yes, sir, but at this hour,
I wouldn't like to bother him.

1148
01:29:22,665 --> 01:29:24,875
He went up to his room
at least two hours ago.

1149
01:29:25,000 --> 01:29:27,336
Have any children been up to see them?

1150
01:29:27,461 --> 01:29:30,005
Yes, but that was a long time ago.

1151
01:29:30,089 --> 01:29:31,882
They wanted to leave something.

1152
01:29:31,966 --> 01:29:33,592
I'm sorry, but this is urgent.

1153
01:29:33,676 --> 01:29:35,219
Would you ask Mr. Palmer if he's seen

1154
01:29:35,302 --> 01:29:37,596
a couple of children this evening?

1155
01:29:37,680 --> 01:29:40,349
He won't like being
disturbed at this hour.

1156
01:29:40,432 --> 01:29:41,267
Please.

1157
01:29:59,285 --> 01:30:00,786
What the devil do you
mean by disturbing me

1158
01:30:00,869 --> 01:30:01,745
at this time of night?

1159
01:30:01,829 --> 01:30:03,872
Are there any
children up there with you?

1160
01:30:03,956 --> 01:30:05,291
Children?

1161
01:30:05,374 --> 01:30:06,500
Don't be absurd, where would I have them,

1162
01:30:06,583 --> 01:30:09,044
under the bed or the closet or something?

1163
01:30:09,128 --> 01:30:10,504
I shall have a word to say about this

1164
01:30:10,629 --> 01:30:11,714
to the manager tomorrow.

1165
01:30:15,676 --> 01:30:16,844
- Basil!
- Yeah?

1166
01:30:16,927 --> 01:30:18,012
You remember what you were telling me

1167
01:30:18,095 --> 01:30:18,846
about here in Hungary,

1168
01:30:18,929 --> 01:30:21,598
the people take the hot showers together?

1169
01:30:21,682 --> 01:30:22,433
Yes?

1170
01:30:22,516 --> 01:30:23,726
Well, can't you arrange one for me

1171
01:30:23,809 --> 01:30:25,227
before we get outta here?

1172
01:30:26,562 --> 01:30:28,564
Oh, there won't be time, Lionel.

1173
01:30:29,815 --> 01:30:33,277
But never mind, you can
have a fine hot bath

1174
01:30:33,360 --> 01:30:35,029
when we get to Japan.

1175
01:30:35,112 --> 01:30:36,030
In Japan?

1176
01:30:36,113 --> 01:30:38,073
Mm-hmm.

1177
01:30:41,785 --> 01:30:42,536
Apart from forcing an entry,

1178
01:30:42,619 --> 01:30:44,872
I don't know what else we can do.

1179
01:30:44,955 --> 01:30:46,165
Where on Earth are they?

1180
01:30:47,583 --> 01:30:49,501
Let's find your father.

1181
01:30:49,585 --> 01:30:50,502
We can try.

1182
01:31:14,568 --> 01:31:16,528
Your London call, Mr. Stevenson.

1183
01:31:16,612 --> 01:31:17,363
Hmm?

1184
01:31:26,330 --> 01:31:27,164
Hello?

1185
01:31:28,082 --> 01:31:29,708
Oh, hello, sir.

1186
01:31:29,792 --> 01:31:31,085
Yes, fine, fine.

1187
01:31:32,086 --> 01:31:33,379
What?

1188
01:31:33,462 --> 01:31:35,672
Oh, yes, I wanted to apologize about that.

1189
01:31:36,882 --> 01:31:37,883
What are you talking about?

1190
01:31:37,966 --> 01:31:40,302
I should apologize for being so late.

1191
01:31:40,386 --> 01:31:42,262
I've been trying to get you all night.

1192
01:31:42,346 --> 01:31:43,472
Quite brilliant of you, you know,

1193
01:31:43,555 --> 01:31:45,599
to recognize Palmer's technique.

1194
01:31:46,517 --> 01:31:47,643
You can bet your bottom dollar

1195
01:31:47,726 --> 01:31:49,311
he's got that Hungarian whatsit.

1196
01:31:50,312 --> 01:31:52,106
Clever idea, getting that picture.

1197
01:31:52,189 --> 01:31:54,316
Bright kids you got there, eh?

1198
01:31:54,400 --> 01:31:56,402
Uh, yes.

1199
01:31:56,527 --> 01:31:59,363
Yeah, well, you give them
a pat on the head from me.

1200
01:31:59,446 --> 01:32:00,948
I hope you get your man.

1201
01:32:01,031 --> 01:32:03,075
Bet the Hungarians are
pleased with you, eh?

1202
01:32:03,158 --> 01:32:05,035
Well, that's all, I just
wanted to let you know

1203
01:32:05,119 --> 01:32:06,954
that we're proud of you.

1204
01:32:07,037 --> 01:32:07,788
Goodbye.

1205
01:32:11,667 --> 01:32:12,501
Goodbye.

1206
01:32:16,588 --> 01:32:17,714
Braithwaite, Braithwaite!

1207
01:32:19,466 --> 01:32:20,259
Braithwaite!

1208
01:32:23,846 --> 01:32:25,597
You know that fellow
the kids were on about?

1209
01:32:25,681 --> 01:32:26,473
Well, he's a criminal.

1210
01:32:26,557 --> 01:32:27,975
He's probably stolen
that golden head thing.

1211
01:32:28,058 --> 01:32:30,436
Impossible, he's English!

1212
01:32:30,519 --> 01:32:31,311
Well, let's face it, old man,

1213
01:32:31,395 --> 01:32:32,479
if there weren't some English crooks,

1214
01:32:32,563 --> 01:32:33,689
I'd be out of business.

1215
01:32:34,565 --> 01:32:35,649
Old man.

1216
01:32:35,732 --> 01:32:37,359
There's only one thing we must do.

1217
01:32:37,443 --> 01:32:38,402
We must nab him ourselves,

1218
01:32:38,485 --> 01:32:39,987
then hand him over to
the Hungarians, right?

1219
01:32:40,070 --> 01:32:41,738
- Right.
- Let's go.

1220
01:32:41,822 --> 01:32:44,366
Oh, just a second, seems
I've forgotten something.

1221
01:32:44,450 --> 01:32:45,742
What?

1222
01:32:45,826 --> 01:32:46,827
Oh, doesn't matter.

1223
01:32:53,959 --> 01:32:55,878
They said he's
he went to the theater,

1224
01:32:55,961 --> 01:32:58,630
and up till now, he hasn't come back yet.

1225
01:32:58,714 --> 01:33:00,090
He must be working late.

1226
01:33:01,133 --> 01:33:03,427
We must go to the police and inform them

1227
01:33:03,510 --> 01:33:04,970
that the children are missing.

1228
01:33:05,053 --> 01:33:06,430
I'm afraid so.

1229
01:33:06,513 --> 01:33:07,639
We'd better get back to the boat

1230
01:33:07,723 --> 01:33:09,057
and wait in case they're found.

1231
01:33:09,141 --> 01:33:10,142
All right.

1232
01:34:05,280 --> 01:34:06,323
Hurry up.

1233
01:34:36,019 --> 01:34:38,313
Tell me which room the children were in!

1234
01:34:38,397 --> 01:34:39,731
What children?

1235
01:34:45,737 --> 01:34:48,323
We've never been out so
early in the morning before.

1236
01:34:48,407 --> 01:34:51,201
Ah, he'll tell us how to
get to the police station.

1237
01:34:51,285 --> 01:34:52,119
Mister!

1238
01:34:53,537 --> 01:34:55,205
We know who's stolen the golden head,

1239
01:34:55,289 --> 01:34:57,082
and we want you to arrest him.

1240
01:35:00,335 --> 01:35:02,629
I guess he doesn't
understand plain English.

1241
01:35:10,137 --> 01:35:10,887
Hi, Dad.

1242
01:35:10,971 --> 01:35:11,930
Where are the children?

1243
01:35:12,014 --> 01:35:12,889
They're lost.

1244
01:35:12,973 --> 01:35:14,433
Not playing detective again!

1245
01:35:14,516 --> 01:35:15,559
I'm afraid so.

1246
01:35:16,643 --> 01:35:18,145
We've told the police.

1247
01:35:18,228 --> 01:35:20,022
Yes, that man Palmer you were on about,

1248
01:35:20,105 --> 01:35:21,273
he's a crook, you know?

1249
01:35:21,356 --> 01:35:23,358
Scotland Yard's identified his photograph.

1250
01:35:23,442 --> 01:35:26,653
That's wonderful, but
what about the children?

1251
01:35:26,737 --> 01:35:28,697
Yes, the truth is they've
gone off to Palmer alone.

1252
01:35:28,780 --> 01:35:29,573
What?

1253
01:35:29,656 --> 01:35:30,741
They left a note.

1254
01:35:30,824 --> 01:35:31,575
He's staying at the Gellert.

1255
01:35:31,658 --> 01:35:33,744
The Gellert, right, come on, after them.

1256
01:35:35,871 --> 01:35:36,872
Oh, dear.

1257
01:35:40,083 --> 01:35:40,834
Well, how'd you like that?

1258
01:35:40,917 --> 01:35:41,877
After all we've been through,

1259
01:35:41,960 --> 01:35:43,837
they go and arrest him by themselves.

1260
01:35:45,088 --> 01:35:46,381
Come on, let's get a taxi.

1261
01:35:50,677 --> 01:35:52,596
Which room is Mr. Palmer in, please?

1262
01:35:54,181 --> 01:35:56,391
244,

1263
01:35:56,475 --> 01:35:58,602
- but don't you disturb him!
- Room 244.

1264
01:36:11,782 --> 01:36:13,116
Ah, here we are.

1265
01:36:13,992 --> 01:36:15,702
Now, both together, Braithwaite.

1266
01:36:15,786 --> 01:36:17,371
One, two...

1267
01:36:21,041 --> 01:36:22,542
Now, come along, Palmer.

1268
01:36:22,626 --> 01:36:25,462
We're handing you over to
the Hungarian authorities.

1269
01:36:25,545 --> 01:36:27,214
Have I had the pleasure?

1270
01:36:27,297 --> 01:36:28,965
Stevenson of Scotland Yard,

1271
01:36:29,049 --> 01:36:31,551
and this is Mr. Braithwaite.

1272
01:36:31,635 --> 01:36:32,636
You're under arrest.

1273
01:36:33,553 --> 01:36:34,763
And what is the charge?

1274
01:36:34,888 --> 01:36:36,848
Stealing the golden head of St. Laszlo,

1275
01:36:36,932 --> 01:36:38,767
which appears to be lying on the bed.

1276
01:36:40,936 --> 01:36:42,604
Don't try anything, Palmer.

1277
01:36:42,688 --> 01:36:44,815
We've both of us played rugby football.

1278
01:36:44,898 --> 01:36:48,151
Ah, but have you ever
played it in a snowstorm?

1279
01:36:48,235 --> 01:36:50,070
What?

1280
01:36:50,195 --> 01:36:51,571
Snowstorm.

1281
01:36:51,697 --> 01:36:53,198
You know, as a matter of fact, I have.

1282
01:36:53,281 --> 01:36:56,076
It was the winter of '38,
I remember it very well.

1283
01:36:56,159 --> 01:36:57,494
It was a grizzly day.

1284
01:36:57,619 --> 01:36:58,453
We were playing against Richmond,

1285
01:36:58,537 --> 01:36:59,496
I was playing for at the time,

1286
01:36:59,621 --> 01:37:00,122
and I came out of the scrimmage...

1287
01:37:00,205 --> 01:37:02,124
- 1938, you say?
- Yes, '38.

1288
01:37:02,249 --> 01:37:03,875
Anyway, I got on.

1289
01:37:17,639 --> 01:37:18,390
Milly!

1290
01:37:22,352 --> 01:37:23,895
Oh, you naughty, naughty children!

1291
01:37:23,979 --> 01:37:25,772
What have you been doing?

1292
01:37:25,856 --> 01:37:27,691
We were so worried about you.

1293
01:37:27,774 --> 01:37:29,234
You shouldn't have been
worried, we were all right.

1294
01:37:29,317 --> 01:37:31,737
I ought to bang your heads together!

1295
01:37:31,820 --> 01:37:33,196
But we planted the head on Palmer.

1296
01:37:33,280 --> 01:37:34,698
We just brought the police.

1297
01:37:34,781 --> 01:37:35,782
We must find Daddy.

1298
01:37:35,866 --> 01:37:37,868
Dad's here, he got here
before the police did.

1299
01:37:37,951 --> 01:37:39,244
Well, let's go and help.

1300
01:37:39,327 --> 01:37:40,579
Okay, but I still think Dad's

1301
01:37:40,662 --> 01:37:42,038
got everything under control.

1302
01:37:45,125 --> 01:37:45,876
Palmer!

1303
01:39:04,496 --> 01:39:05,497
There he is!

1304
01:39:12,087 --> 01:39:14,798
There's the right way
now, come on, let's get out.

1305
01:39:24,683 --> 01:39:25,725
Mr. Stevenson!

1306
01:39:27,185 --> 01:39:28,854
Looks like you're in a snowstorm.

1307
01:39:28,937 --> 01:39:29,771
Oh, thank heaven you're here.

1308
01:39:29,855 --> 01:39:31,273
Palmer just got away with the head.

1309
01:39:31,356 --> 01:39:33,608
I understand Scotland Yard
recognized the photographs.

1310
01:39:33,692 --> 01:39:35,151
Congratulations.

1311
01:39:35,235 --> 01:39:37,696
Oh, it's just routine stuff.

1312
01:39:56,631 --> 01:39:58,592
There they are, and the children.

1313
01:39:58,675 --> 01:39:59,593
After them.

1314
01:40:01,261 --> 01:40:03,722
Come on, Milly, come on!

1315
01:40:24,826 --> 01:40:25,869
Back to the car.

1316
01:40:25,952 --> 01:40:27,746
And for heaven's sake, all
of you, just stay here.

1317
01:40:27,829 --> 01:40:29,998
Just stay here till I
come back and get you.

1318
01:40:36,212 --> 01:40:37,297
Oh, there's my friend.

1319
01:40:39,883 --> 01:40:40,800
Who is he?

1320
01:40:40,884 --> 01:40:42,177
Oh, he's all right, come on.

1321
01:41:17,462 --> 01:41:18,964
This is beautiful!

1322
01:41:19,047 --> 01:41:22,092
When we sell the head, why
don't we get one of these?

1323
01:41:22,175 --> 01:41:24,010
Well, I prefer a convertible.

1324
01:41:24,094 --> 01:41:25,679
Oh, well...

1325
01:42:29,993 --> 01:42:31,578
Come on now, let's get out here.

1326
01:42:31,661 --> 01:42:32,912
Oh, no, really!

1327
01:42:34,581 --> 01:42:38,501
Come on, come on, get
the train, get the train!

1328
01:43:58,206 --> 01:43:59,040
Come on!

1329
01:44:03,753 --> 01:44:05,171
There they are!

1330
01:44:06,881 --> 01:44:08,341
Come on, after them!

1331
01:44:26,317 --> 01:44:28,027
Well, you wanted to see the city.

1332
01:44:28,111 --> 01:44:29,612
Now take a good look.

1333
01:44:46,629 --> 01:44:51,593
We can catch them on the
side of the river.

1334
01:44:59,767 --> 01:45:02,228
Come on, back in the car, come on!

1335
01:46:38,324 --> 01:46:40,243
Oh, that's all we need!

1336
01:46:42,412 --> 01:46:43,413
Get on with it!

1337
01:46:46,666 --> 01:46:47,959
Back in the car.

1338
01:48:11,042 --> 01:48:11,793
Shut up!

1339
01:48:28,643 --> 01:48:32,480
Gentlemen, I have the most
wonderful news for you.

1340
01:48:32,563 --> 01:48:35,942
We have recovered the
golden head of St. Laszlo.

1341
01:48:43,533 --> 01:48:45,660
That's him, you might
as well give up now.

1342
01:48:45,743 --> 01:48:47,662
Oh, pay no attention, Lionel.

1343
01:48:47,745 --> 01:48:49,247
I take it that there is a reward

1344
01:48:49,330 --> 01:48:50,540
for the return of this priceless...

1345
01:48:50,665 --> 01:48:52,583
You can't do that!

1346
01:48:57,255 --> 01:48:59,966
Palmer, you're under arrest.

1347
01:49:01,634 --> 01:49:02,468
Oh.

1348
01:49:03,928 --> 01:49:07,140
Gentlemen, I think you should know

1349
01:49:07,223 --> 01:49:09,684
that without this young girl's help,

1350
01:49:09,809 --> 01:49:13,146
we should never have got
our golden head back again.

1351
01:49:13,229 --> 01:49:14,147
It was nothing.

1352
01:49:16,023 --> 01:49:18,985
Gentlemen, do not allow
yourselves to be swayed

1353
01:49:19,068 --> 01:49:20,653
by deceptive appearances.

1354
01:49:20,736 --> 01:49:22,321
I can explain everything.

1355
01:49:22,405 --> 01:49:24,532
You've got as much chance
talking us out of this

1356
01:49:24,615 --> 01:49:26,909
as you got at talking us
into Buckingham Palace.

1357
01:49:32,790 --> 01:49:35,668
Her Majesty has graciously
consented to receive you.

1358
01:49:35,751 --> 01:49:38,087
If you will come this way.

1359
01:49:44,469 --> 01:49:45,845
Daddy, that's Palmer.

1360
01:49:45,928 --> 01:49:47,054
Milly!

1361
01:49:47,138 --> 01:49:48,431
I, I should know.

1362
01:49:48,514 --> 01:49:51,184
Milly, for heaven's sake,
don't start that nonsense again.

1363
01:49:59,609 --> 01:50:03,196
Inspector Stevenson and his
daughter, Millicent, ma'am.

1364
01:50:13,247 --> 01:50:16,083
Ma'am, that man out there
is a well-known crook,

1365
01:50:16,167 --> 01:50:16,959
Basil Palmer.

1366
01:50:17,043 --> 01:50:18,753
Milly, for heaven's sake!

1367
01:50:22,632 --> 01:50:23,341
Lionel.

1368
01:50:23,424 --> 01:50:24,175
Yeah?

1369
01:50:24,258 --> 01:50:25,593
Time we started traveling again.

1370
01:50:25,676 --> 01:50:28,012
Wonderful, Japan will be
lovely this time of year.
